g.text: You: "You think this will make them cooperate?"

Kim Kitsuragi: "Nothing will make them respect the RCM. But it will disrupt the game they prepared for us. We just stripped off one layer of whatever it is. Her decision to not corroborate their story was *definitely* not part of the plan."
Volition: Like hell you would have -- remember?
Kim Kitsuragi: "You think so?" A shadow runs across his face. "She seemed forthcoming... Unusually so. Being forthcoming about some things is a good way to obscure other things."
Kim Kitsuragi: "The best liars are always forthcoming... Anyway, we should move. I suspect our investigation will bring us back here soon enough."
You: "I'm not sure she *had* to lie. I wouldn't have known."
Kim Kitsuragi: "If not you, then me. It was a smart move from her."

Kim Kitsuragi: "You think so?" A shadow runs across his face. "Being candid is the best way to lie. The appearance of candour, with some facts thrown in, draws attention away from whatever one chooses to omit."
Kim Kitsuragi: "She may be trying to control the pace of the investigation. Anyway, we should move. I suspect our inquiries will bring us back here soon enough."
Kim Kitsuragi: "I am not easily swayed by young women. But on the other hand... the best liars are candid. And she was candid."
Kim Kitsuragi: "She seemed forthcoming to me... Unusually so. Being forthcoming with some things is a good way to obscure other things. But I wouldn't call myself compromised..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Anyway, we should move. I suspect our investigation will bring us back soon enough."
Drama: You would have caught it.
Kim Kitsuragi: "So you said to her.... What did you *mean* by it?"
You: (Whisper.) "She has half my skillset compromised, singing her tune. My assessments of her are untrustworthy."
Kim Kitsuragi: "What do you mean by that?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "What else could she have done? Lie? She saw there was no way to lie and get away with it."
You: "I have reason to doubt my ability to see through her lies."
Volition: The lieutenant seems oddly sure he is not compromised, not psychologically at least. Is it hubris?
You: (Say in a hushed voice.) "Why *did* she tell us all of that?"
